<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="1130" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[178,1085,805,857]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130">Etymology: The specific epithet (adjective) alludes to the pronounced crista apicalis of the aedeagus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="1133" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[178,1085,872,982]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130">
Description: Body length 
<quantity box="[541,662,872,894]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.15" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130" unit="mm" value="3.15" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.8">2.8-3.5 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity box="[873,995,872,894]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130" unit="mm" value="1.4" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.3">1.3-1.5 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[244,325,901,923]" captionStart="Figs 34-42" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1507,1529]" captionTargetBox="[187,1076,212,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-75@13.[178,1085,212,1485]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 34-42: Oxypoda grandicristata nov.sp.: (34) habitus; (35) forebody; (36) antenna; (37-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) paramere; (41-42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 34: 1.0 mm; 35: 0.5 mm; 36-42: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183274" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183274/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
. Coloration: body more or less uniformly brown to dark-brown; legs reddish; antennae brown, with the basal 2-4 antennomeres usually more or less distinctly paler; maxillary palpi reddish with palpomere III brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[178,1085,997,1225]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[246,321,997,1019]" captionStart="Figs 34-42" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1507,1529]" captionTargetBox="[187,1076,212,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-75@13.[178,1085,212,1485]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 34-42: Oxypoda grandicristata nov.sp.: (34) habitus; (35) forebody; (36) antenna; (37-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) paramere; (41-42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 34: 1.0 mm; 35: 0.5 mm; 36-42: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183274" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183274/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) approximately as broad as long; punctation dense and distinct; interstices with shallow microreticulation. Eyes small, approximately half as long as postocular region in dorsal view and not protruding from lateral contours of head. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[1003,1077,1056,1078]" captionStart="Figs 34-42" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1507,1529]" captionTargetBox="[187,1076,212,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-75@13.[178,1085,212,1485]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 34-42: Oxypoda grandicristata nov.sp.: (34) habitus; (35) forebody; (36) antenna; (37-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) paramere; (41-42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 34: 1.0 mm; 35: 0.5 mm; 36-42: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183274" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183274/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[178,297,1086,1107]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130" unit="mm" value="0.85" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.8">0.8-0.9 mm</quantity>
long and distinctly incrassate apically; antennomeres IV weakly transverse, V-IX distinctly transverse and more than 1.5 times as broad as long, X 1.5 times as long as IX and barely 1.5 times as broad as long, and XI oval, less than twice as long as broad and approximately as long as the combined length of IX and X. Maxillary palpomere III stout, less than three times as long as broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[178,1085,1240,1321]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[294,370,1240,1262]" captionStart="Figs 34-42" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1507,1529]" captionTargetBox="[187,1076,212,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-75@13.[178,1085,212,1485]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 34-42: Oxypoda grandicristata nov.sp.: (34) habitus; (35) forebody; (36) antenna; (37-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) paramere; (41-42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 34: 1.0 mm; 35: 0.5 mm; 36-42: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183274" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183274/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) rather strongly convex in cross-section, approximately 1.2 times as broad as long and 1.4 times as broad as head, broadest behind middle; punctation dense and rather fine; interstices with shallow microreticulation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[178,1085,1337,1512]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130">
Elytra (
<figureCitation box="[254,328,1337,1359]" captionStart="Figs 34-42" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1507,1529]" captionTargetBox="[187,1076,212,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-75@13.[178,1085,212,1485]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 34-42: Oxypoda grandicristata nov.sp.: (34) habitus; (35) forebody; (36) antenna; (37-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) paramere; (41-42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 34: 1.0 mm; 35: 0.5 mm; 36-42: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183274" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183274/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) rather short, 0.80-0.85 times as long as pronotum; punctation very dense, more distinct than that of head and pronotum; interstices with shallow microsculpture; posterior margin moderately sinuate near postero-lateral angles. Hind wings completely reduced. Legs moderately slender; metatibia approximately 
<quantity box="[819,901,1429,1450]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="1130" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
long; metatarsus nearly as long as metatibia; metatarsomere I approximately as long as the combined length of metatarsomeres II-IV.
</paragraph>
