<paragraph blockId="14.[178,1085,845,959]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">Abdomen with segments III-VI of subequal width, segments VII and VIII weakly tapering posteriad; punctation distinct, very dense on tergites III-VI, somewhat less dense on tergites VII and VIII; interstices without microsculpture; posterior margin of tergite VII with rudiment of a palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[178,1086,974,1121]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">
♂: sternite VIII with convex posterior margin; median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[962,1078,976,998]" captionStart="Figs 34-42" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1507,1529]" captionTargetBox="[187,1076,212,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-75@13.[178,1085,212,1485]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 34-42: Oxypoda grandicristata nov.sp.: (34) habitus; (35) forebody; (36) antenna; (37-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) paramere; (41-42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 34: 1.0 mm; 35: 0.5 mm; 36-42: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183274" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183274/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">Figs 37-39</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[178,322,1007,1028]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133" unit="mm" value="0.38" valueMax="0.39" valueMin="0.37">0.37-0.39 mm</quantity>
long and of conspicuous shape; ventral process strongly arched in lateral view, apex undivided and very slender in ventral view; crista apicalis enormous; paramere (
<figureCitation box="[245,321,1068,1090]" captionStart="Figs 34-42" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1507,1529]" captionTargetBox="[187,1076,212,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-75@13.[178,1085,212,1485]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 34-42: Oxypoda grandicristata nov.sp.: (34) habitus; (35) forebody; (36) antenna; (37-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) paramere; (41-42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 34: 1.0 mm; 35: 0.5 mm; 36-42: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183274" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183274/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
) much longer than median lobe, approximately 
<quantity box="[824,904,1068,1089]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
long, apical lobe slender and long, but less than half as long as basal portion.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[178,1085,1137,1221]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">
<specimenCount box="[178,191,1141,1164]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: posterior margin of sternite VIII weakly convex, in the middle truncate or weakly concave, with long marginal setae; spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[716,834,1168,1190]" captionStart="Figs 34-42" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1507,1529]" captionTargetBox="[187,1076,212,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-75@13.[178,1085,212,1485]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 34-42: Oxypoda grandicristata nov.sp.: (34) habitus; (35) forebody; (36) antenna; (37-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) paramere; (41-42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 34: 1.0 mm; 35: 0.5 mm; 36-42: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183274" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183274/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">Figs 41-42</figureCitation>
) of somewhat variable shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="1134" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[178,1085,1237,1597]" lastBlockId="15.[178,1085,220,334]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="1134" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">
Comparative notes: Representatives of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="THOMSON, 1859" authorityName="THOMSON" authorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bessopora">
<emphasis box="[861,968,1238,1259]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">Bessopora</emphasis>
THOMSON, 1859
</taxonomicName>
were previously unknown from 
<collectingCountry box="[569,661,1268,1290]" name="Armenia" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">Armenia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2016" box="[672,916,1268,1289]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandicristata">
<emphasis box="[672,916,1268,1289]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">Oxypoda grandicristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from nearly all of the widespread representatives of this subgenus by the short elytra and the absence of fully developed hind wings and from all its congeners by the conspicuous morphology of the median lobe of the aedeagus. The shape of the median lobe somewhat resembles that of 
<taxonomicName authority="KRAATZ, 1856" authorityName="KRAATZ" authorityYear="1856" box="[359,646,1390,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recondita">
<emphasis box="[359,488,1391,1412]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">O. recondita</emphasis>
KRAATZ, 1856
</taxonomicName>
, which is listed in the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[977,1085,1391,1412]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">Baeoglena</emphasis>
THOMSON, 
<quantity box="[295,373,1421,1443]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.74218" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133" unit="in" value="1867.0">1867 in</quantity>
SCHÜLKE &amp; SMETANA (2015). This subgeneric assignment is clearly erroneous and based on a homoplasy (elongate maxillary palpomere III); other external characters and the morphology of the aedeagus suggest that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KRAATZ" authorityYear="1856" box="[831,964,1483,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recondita">
<emphasis box="[831,964,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">O. recondita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="THOMSON" authorityYear="1859" box="[178,285,1514,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="1136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bessopora">
<emphasis box="[178,285,1514,1535]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">Bessopora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Aside from the short elytra and the absence of hind wings, the new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KRAATZ" authorityYear="1856" box="[314,446,1544,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recondita">
<emphasis box="[314,446,1544,1565]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1133">O. recondita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by darker coloration, more distinct punctation of the whole body, shorter antennae with more transverse antennomeres V-IX, the shape of the male sternite VIII (
<taxonomicName authorityName="KRAATZ" authorityYear="1856" box="[325,457,220,241]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recondita">
<emphasis box="[325,457,220,241]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. recondita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: posteriorly distinctly pointed), and the morphology of the aedeagus (median lobe smaller; ventral process more strongly arched in lateral view and with more slender apex in ventral view; crista apicalis larger; paramere with longer and basally not distinctly dilated apical lobe).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[178,1085,350,465]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">
Distribution and natural history: The 
<typeStatus box="[835,871,351,372]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">type</typeStatus>
locality is situated near Jermuk in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[437,526,381,403]" name="Armenia" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Armenia</collectingCountry>
at an altitude of approximately 
<quantity box="[863,944,381,402]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" unit="m" value="2100.0">2100 m</quantity>
. The reduced hind wings suggest that the distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2016" box="[626,804,412,433]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandicristata">
<emphasis box="[626,804,412,433]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. grandicristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably restricted. The specimens were sifted from leaf litter in, and at the margin of, an oak forest (
<figureCitation box="[956,1033,442,465]" captionStart="Figs 43" captionStartId="14.[178,218,808,830]" captionTargetBox="[178,1059,212,799]" captionTargetId="figure-351@14.[178,1059,212,799]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 43: Type locality of Oxypoda grandicristata nov.sp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183276/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
